# Next.js App Router Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 14+ App Router
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Prisma + PostgreSQL
- NextAuth.js / Clerk for auth

## App Router Conventions
- Server Components by default — add `"use client"` only when needed
- Route handlers in `app/api/<route>/route.ts`
- Loading states with `loading.tsx`, errors with `error.tsx`
- Metadata via `generateMetadata()` — never put <head> tags manually
- `generateStaticParams()` for static routes

## Server vs Client Components
Server Component (default): data fetching, db calls, heavy computation
Client Component (`"use client"`): onClick, useState, useEffect, browser APIs

## Data Fetching
- `fetch()` with `{ next: { revalidate: N } }` for ISR
- `{ cache: 'no-store' }` for dynamic data
- Server Actions for mutations — no separate API routes for simple CRUD

## File Conventions
- Page: `app/<route>/page.tsx`
- Layout: `app/<route>/layout.tsx`
- Components: `components/<Name>/<Name>.tsx`
- Server actions: `app/actions/<feature>.ts`
- Types: `types/<domain>.ts`

## Performance
- Use `next/image` for all images
- Use `next/font` for fonts — no Google Fonts CDN links
- Dynamic import components not needed on first paint
